---
import LegalLayout from "../layouts/LegalLayout.astro"
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Refund Policy"
  description="Learn about Botyoo's billing terms, cancellations, and refund eligibility policies."
>
  <h1 class="text-foreground mb-6 text-3xl font-bold">Refund Policy</h1>
  <p class="mb-4"><strong>Effective Date:</strong> 2025-05-08</p>

  <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-8">
    At botyoo.com, we prioritize transparency and customer satisfaction. This
    Refund Policy outlines when and how users may be eligible for a refund
    related to our Instagram automation services.
  </p>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-foreground mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">1. Free Trial</h2>
    <p class="text-muted-foreground">We offer a free trial period to allow users to evaluate our platform before subscribing. Please use this period to ensure our features meet your needs.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-foreground mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">2. Eligibility for Refunds</h2>
    <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">You may be eligible for a full or partial refund if:</p>
    <ul class="text-muted-foreground mb-4 list-disc pl-6">
      <li>You submit a written refund request within 7 days of the initial purchase</li>
      <li>You experience a verifiable technical issue that prevents access or use of core features (not caused by incorrect setup or third-party platform limits)</li>
      <li>You have not violated any part of our Terms of Service</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-foreground mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">3. Non-Refundable Situations</h2>
    <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">Refunds will not be issued in these cases:</p>
    <ul class="text-muted-foreground mb-4 list-disc pl-6">
      <li>Subscription renewals were not canceled before the billing cycle</li>
      <li>Services were partially used after the subscription period started</li>
      <li>Limitations due to Meta (Instagram/Facebook) platform changes, bans, or API deprecations</li>
      <li>Violation of our Terms of Service, spam/abuse, or account restrictions</li>
      <li>One-time services such as onboarding, support, or consulting</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-foreground mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">4. How to Request a Refund</h2>
    <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">Please send your refund request to <strong class="text-foreground">hevin@botyoo.com</strong> and include:</p>
    <ul class="text-muted-foreground mb-4 list-disc pl-6">
      <li>The email address associated with your Botyoo account</li>
      <li>Transaction ID or billing reference</li>
      <li>Reason for the refund request and supporting details</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-muted-foreground">Refund requests will be evaluated within 5–7 business days, and eligible refunds will be processed to the original payment method within 7–10 business days.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-foreground mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">5. Contact</h2>
    <p class="text-muted-foreground">📧 <strong class="text-foreground">hevin@botyoo.com</strong></p>
  </section>
</LegalLayout>
